.13798739,-0.01933027,-0.00282730,0.02302742,-0.03365045,0.06167811,0.01551544,0.03550242,0.00790520,0.00619010,0.04276866,-0.00483451,0.09652258,-0.06730559,0.03800183,-0.00620947,-0.00182050,-0.01694575,-0.07123201,-0.01398065,-0.02176004,-0.00773466,0.03951578,0.03181579,-0.06235589,-0.04147949,-0.02924159,0.04890202,-0.02017499,-0.06262715,-0.01229807,-0.02139808,-0.01243422,0.01316941,0.00842170,-0.07407634,-0.15153359,-0.00273715,0.00291370,0.03437506,0.01381081,0.04353189,-0.01402102]',E'RouteChain\n\nWhen several HTTP methods share the **same path**, [`RouteChain`](../api/app.md#routechain) lets you declare the path once and chain the verb handlers. An `All` in the chain runs before the verb handlers on that path, acting as route-specific middleware.\n\n```go\napp.RouteChain("/events").\n    All(func(c fiber.Ctx) error { return c.Next() }). // route-local middleware\n    Get(func(c fiber.Ctx) error { return c.SendString("GET /events") }).\n    Post(func(c fiber.Ctx) error { return c.SendString("POST /events") })\n```\n\n:::note\nWithin a chain, `All` registers prefix-matched middleware (like [`app.Use`](../api/app.md#use)), not the exact-path `App.All`, so it also runs for sub-paths of the chain path.\n:::','{"source": "go-fiber", "version": "3.3", "language": "go", "title": "Grouping", "section_title": "grouping", "url": "https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/main/docs/guide/grouping.md", "topics": "fiber,http,grouping", "categories": "web,go,rest"}');
