9,-0.00318259,-0.00093587,0.02918681,-0.00093265,-0.02323151,0.07132691,-0.00478160,0.03178196,0.02368989,0.01442565,-0.03505849,0.03540734,-0.08700118,0.01058736,0.01034460,-0.01463436,-0.08272890,0.00329354,0.04224402,-0.04556154,-0.02936444,0.03103203,-0.06086720,-0.00104382,-0.01860081,-0.04201586,0.03632151,0.04778756,-0.02068079,-0.00241879,-0.04287301,-0.00050351,0.00594144,-0.00635673,-0.02298623,-0.07164848,0.04355339,0.01751339,-0.04204186,0.10882795,-0.00755790,0.00730850]',E'Catching Errors\n\nReturn errors from route handlers and middleware so Fiber can handle them centrally.\n\n<Tabs>\n<TabItem value="example" label="Example">\n\n```go\napp.Get("/", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n    // Pass error to Fiber\n    return c.SendFile("file-does-not-exist")\n})\n```\n\n</TabItem>\n</Tabs>\n\nFiber does not recover from [panics](https://go.dev/blog/defer-panic-and-recover) by default. Add the `Recover` middleware to catch panics in any handler:\n\n```go title="Example"\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    "log"','{"source": "go-fiber", "version": "3.3", "language": "go", "title": "Error Handling", "section_title": "error-handling", "url": "https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/main/docs/guide/error-handling.md", "topics": "fiber,http,error,handling", "categories": "web,go,rest"}');
