57,0.00578083,0.09859583,0.01877319,-0.03565599,0.05361110,0.04725763,-0.02836878,0.00358344,-0.02705465,0.06150309,-0.03808744,0.08691590,-0.10793793,0.05723946,0.01457974,0.00190290,-0.07178663,-0.03553647,0.02402863,-0.03186774,-0.03549685,0.04664031,-0.01265377,0.00011790,-0.02699023,-0.00980224,0.03979340,-0.00482778,-0.04964871,-0.02927365,-0.01835977,-0.00089104,0.02922012,-0.03669988,-0.03547338,-0.09646855,-0.00214290,0.04268384,-0.00876353,0.10864510,-0.01745082,0.01661116]',E'RestartRouting\n\nInstead of executing the next method when calling [Next](ctx.md#next), **RestartRouting** restarts execution from the first method that matches the current route. This may be helpful after overriding the path, i.e., an internal redirect. Note that handlers might be executed again, which could result in an infinite loop.\n\n```go title="Signature"\nfunc (c fiber.Ctx) RestartRouting() error\n```\n\n```go title="Example"\napp.Get("/new", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n  return c.SendString("From /new")\n})\n\napp.Get("/old", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n  c.Path("/new")\n  return c.RestartRouting()\n})\n```','{"source": "go-fiber", "version": "3.3", "language": "go", "title": "Ctx", "section_title": "ctx", "url": "https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/main/docs/api/ctx.md", "topics": "fiber,http,ctx", "categories": "web,go,rest"}');
